<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:lang="en" xml:id="element-table" class="element"
	xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/dml/1.0/"
	xmlns:cdml="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/cdml/1.0/"
	xmlns:dct="http://purl.org/dc/terms/">

	<title>The <cdml:node role="element">table</cdml:node> element</title>
	<metadata>
		<list>
			<item property="dct:description">A table container.</item>
		</list>
	</metadata>
	<p>The <cdml:node role="element">table</cdml:node> element represents a table container.</p>
	<list>
		<item>
			<title>Flow</title>
			<p href="#block-flow">Block</p>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Children</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( title?, summary, group+ )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Attributes</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( $core.attrs* | $meta.attrs* | @scope )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Parents</title>
			<cdml:code language="xpath">
( dml | $block[$block] )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
	</list>

	<p>The <cdml:node role="attribute">scope</cdml:node> attribute <em>must</em> be used to provide the primary scope of groups. Allowed values are: <cdml:value>row</cdml:value> and <cdml:value>column</cdml:value>.</p>

